AN INTRODUCTION :
=================
The Reader who discovers MEFISTO has to read the set of this documentation.
The notions of POINTS, LINES, SURFACES, VOLUMES, OBJECTS are explained
in the following paragrah.
The using notice of MENUS is described in the paragraph MENUS.
The Reader who hesitates on the input of a value or a User's function 
may come to the paragraphs MENUS, NUMERICAL INPUT, GRAMMAR of LU language
and especially the EXAMPLES which follow.
The available KEY WORDS of this menu are described in the last paragraph.

THE GEOMETRIC PRIMITIVES:
========================= 
Every OBJECT to be MESHED has to be decomposed into 
POINTS, LINES, SURFACES, VOLUMES, ( in an abbreviated form PLSV ).
After, to add the materials, the boundary conditions and the interpolation
the PLSV are grouped to form the OBJECT for the computing.

The extremities of one PLSV are described from the previous:
The POINTS   are defined from their coordinates or mapping of an initial point.
The LINES    (often CURVES) are defined often from their extremities: POINTS.
The SURFACES are defined often from their extremities: LINES.
The VOLUMES  are defined often from their extremities: SURFACES.
                                  
By notation, a PLSV is indefferently a POINT or a LINE or a SURFACE or a VOLUME.
A PLSV may not be a blend of POINTS, LINES, SURFACES, VOLUMES.
But, a PLSV may be an UNION of same type PLSV.
For example, an UNION of LINES    is a LINE
             an UNION of SURFACES is a SURFACE ...

Every PLSV definition requierts a MAPPING.
Generally, this MAPPING is reduced to IDENTITY noted I.
In other cases, the MAPPING permits the construction of curved PLSV or
DEFORMED or DISPLACED ou SYMETRIC ou PROJETED PLSV... 

An OBJECT is the UNION without MAPPING of POINTS,LINES,SURFACES,VOLUMES and
OBJECTS. The numerical computing (heat transfer, elasticity, wave,...)
is done from one OBJECT.  

Every PLSV or OBJECT is IDENTIFIED by a NAME of up to 24 CHARACTERS,
choosen by the User. All data arrays of PLSVO are identified from these names.

PHYSICAL DATA:
==============
The comportement of materials is charaterized by some input
(conductivity, module de Young,...). These data are linked
to the PLSV which support them. A conductivity to a volume, a pressure
on a surface, a fixation at a point, ...
A vocabulary is associated to data for each type of problem (heat transfer, 
elasticity, wave, ...) Cf the initial documentation of the first menu of
THERMICER, ELASTICER, FLUIDER.

THE LOGICAL ORDER TO CONSTRUCT A FINITE ELEMENT MESH:
=====================================================
2 TYPES of MESHES : STRUCTURED or UNSTRUCTURED.
In all cases, the 3 coordinates of VERTICES of FINITE ELEMENT (FE) are stored.
A STRUCTURED MESH is characterized by some integers:
line of N consecutive points,
quadrangle of NX edges in a direction "X" and NY in an other direction "Y"
hexahedron of NX edges in a direction "X", NY in direction "Y", 
              NZ in direction "Z3

An UNSTRUCTURED MESH is described by the list of node numbers of every FE.

The top-down analysis leads to choose:

- for every VOLUME an algorithm programmed in Mefisto which induces data
often a list of SURFACES (as the boundary of the volume);

- for every SURFACE an algorithm programmed in Mefisto which induces data
often a list of LINES (as the boundary of the surface) or SURFACES;

- for every LINE an algorithm programmed in Mefisto which induces data
often a list of POINTS (as interpolation points) or LINES;

A synthesis gives the list of POINTS, LINES, SURFACES, VOLUMES.

Remark: The intersection of 2 FE must be the empty set, or a vertex,
or the totality of an edge, or the totality of a triangular or quadrangular face.
Else, the mesh is NOT CORRECT, NOT CONFORM.

With this analysis, a PLS common at 2 PLSV is construct once and referred
many times and the CONFORMITY is obtained.

The bottom-up construction leads to type:

- the POINTS either the typing of 3 coordinates, or the using of the mouse
in 2d or 3d.

- the LINES from the data of its type (straight line, arc of circle, 
B-spline, ...), the number of edges of the line, the distribution of vertices,
regular or defined with a geometrical ratio of edge lengths.

- the SURFACES from the data of its type (square, circle, B-spline, ...),
the list of LINES of their boundary,...


- the VOLUMES from the data of its type (hexahedron, polyhedron, ...),
the list of SURFACES of their boundary,...

A PLSV can be the result of a MAPPING ( translation, rotation,
dilatation, mathematical expression from R3 to R3, projection, symetries,...) 

After, the OBJECT is defined from POINTS, LINES, SURFACES, VOLUMES in order
to associate their PHYSICAL CHARATERISTICS, the BOUNDARY CONDITIONS.

Thus, the choice of FE is done by the degree of Lagrange polynomials used.
During this operation, the nodes will be renumbered to reduce the storage
of the future skyline matrices.

THE MENUS :
===========
The start of the execution produces a menu of options.

2 possibilities are offered:
1. displace the mouse arrow to the rectangle of the chosen option and click
   one of the 3 buttoms of the mouse => the option is executed
2. type on keyboard the integer number written in the rectangle, and 
   the character ";" and "return" => the option is executed
A computation is done or a new menu appears. And so on ...

To abandon the option, type @;  or Escape or click the rectangle @; Escape...

ATTENTION: The typing of @;  suppresses all data input data, in particular
the preceding data of the line!

To obtain the documentation, type ?;  or click the rectangle DOCUMENTATION

THE NUMERICAL INPUT and USER LANGUAGE LU:
=========================================
These input (integer, real, real2 (double precision), logical, characters,...)
are typed on the keyboard and FINISHED by the 2 characters  ;  return

The typing of ? gives the documentation of the value which is requested,
then indicates the type of the value and its actual value if it exists
a default value. If this value is correct, type = to accept it.

All text between the characters is a comment.
{ comment } is not taken in account by the User Language (LU).

For LU, upper or lower cases of letters are equal.

This language permits to type on keyboard at any time
- a numerical value :  3;  -2E-3;
- an algebraic expression to be evaluated :  3.14159 * 2.71828 ;
- a declaration of variables : defvar pi,radius, nb_edges;
- the value of a pre-defined variable : radius = 1.2; pi=atan(1) * 4.0;
- the declaration of a function : deffunc aire( r );
                                  aire = pi * r ** 2 ;
                                  endfunc;
- the evaluation of a function : aire( 10.345 );  aire( rayon/ 7);

For more precisions, cf the LU grammar and examples which followed;
                            
ATTENTION: DO NOT FORGET to SAVE the DATA ARRAYS by the typing of 
99; SAVE DATA and QUIT
else, ALL IS LOST!!!...
Type CTRL C leads to the same LOST! 


A REMARK ON THE MANAGEMENT OF FILES:
====================================
Every DATA is stored in a SECONDARY MEMORY (MS) formed from some DIRECT 
ACCESS FILES ON DISK.
If space is not sufficient, it is possible to add a new file.

The LU LANGUAGE GRAMMAR:
========================
Every NUMERICAL VALUE (integer, real, double real ) or CHARACTER STRING
must be done with respect to the rules of the grammar defined below:

The number of blank between words is not significant, excepted for a
string of characters <STRING of CHARACTERS>.

<DONNEE> :=  | <KEY_WORD> ;
             | <STRING of CHARACTERS> ; 
             | defvar <IDENT_VAR>{,<IDENT_VAR>} ;
             | <FONCTION_D> ; 
             | <VALEUR_D>   ; 

<KEY_WORD> := | { COMMENTAIRE }
              | @        abandon of input, up a level in the tree of menus
                         ATTENTION: The typing of @; or ESCAPE do not permit 
                                    the analysis of data on this line, even
                                    data before this character!
             | ?         display the documentation for this input
                                 eventually its actual value
             | =        keep the actual value
             | QUITTER  the actual input file without close it
             | EXIT     the actual input file without close it
             | FERMER   quit the actual input file and close it
             | CLOSE    quit the actual input file and close it
             | LIREF nom_de_fichier   nom  dependant de l'utilisateur
             | READF name_of_file     name dependent of the user

<STRING of CHARACTERS> := | '<CHARACTER>{<CHARACTER>}'
                          | '<CHARACTER>{''{<CHARACTER>}}'

<FONCTION_D> :=  DefFunc <IDENT_FONC>(<PARAM>{,<PARAM>});
                {defvar  <NOM_VAR>{,<NOM_VAR>} ; }
                {defetiq <ETIQ>{,<ETIQ>} ; }
                {ETIQ :} <INSTRUCTION>
               {{ETIQ :} <INSTRUCTION> }
                {ETIQ :}  EndFunc ;

<INSTRUCTION> := | <IDENT_FONC> = <EXPR_D> ;
                 | <NOM_VAR>    = <EXPR_D> ;
                 | afficher <EXPR_D>{,<EXPR_D>} ;
                 | if       <EXPR_LOGIQ> 
                   then    <INSTRUCTION>
                  {else    <INSTRUCTION>}
                   endif ;
                 | pour <NOM_VAR> = <EXPR_D>  a  <EXPR_D> ;
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   finpour ;
                 | repeter ;
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   jusque  <EXPR_LOGIQ> ;
                 | tantque <EXPR_LOGIQ> ;
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   fintant ;
                 | retour ;
                 | aller <ETIQ> ;

                 | display  <EXPR_D>{,<EXPR_D>} ;
                 | if       <EXPR_LOGIQ> 
                   then    <INSTRUCTION>
                  {else    <INSTRUCTION>}
                   endif ;
                 | for <NOM_VAR> = <EXPR_D>  to  <EXPR_D> ;  the step is 1
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   endfor ;
                 | repeat ;
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   until  <EXPR_LOGIQ> ;
                 | while <EXPR_LOGIQ> ;
                      <INSTRUCTION>
                   endwhile ;
                 | return ;
                 | goto <ETIQ> ;

<VALEUR_D>   := | <EXPR_D> 
                | <IDENT_VAR> = <EXPR_D>  

<EXPR_D>     := | (<EXPR_D>)
                | <TERME>
                | <TERME> + <EXPR_D>  
                | <TERME> - <EXPR_D>  

<TERME>      := | <FACTEUR>
                | <FACTEUR> * <TERME>    
                | <FACTEUR> / <TERME>    

<FACTEUR>    := | <PUISSANCE>
                | <PUISSANCE> ** <EXPR_D> 
 
<PUISSANCE>  := | <EXPR_D>
                | <VARIABLE>  

<VARIABLE>   := | <CONSTANTE_D>
                | <IDENT_VAR>
                | <VARIABLE_TMS>
                | <IDENT_FONC>(<EXPR_D>{,<EXPR_D>) 
  
In the definition deffunc of a function,<VARIABLE> may be 
a parameter <PARAM> of the function.

<EXPR_LOGIQ> := | <EXPR_LOGI>  ox  <EXPR_LOGIQ>    or exclusif      
                | <EXPR_LOGIQ> ox  <EXPR_LOGI>   

<EXPR_LOGI>  := | <EXPR_LOG>   ou  <EXPR_LOGIQ>    or inclusif
                | <EXPR_LOGIQ> ou  <EXPR_LOG>  
                | <EXPR_LOG>   or  <EXPR_LOGIQ>
                | <EXPR_LOGIQ> or  <EXPR_LOG>

<EXPR_LOG>   := | <EXPR_LO>    et  <EXPR_LOGIQ>  
                | <EXPR_LOGIQ> et  <EXPR_LO>
                | <EXPR_LO>    and <EXPR_LOGIQ>  
                | <EXPR_LOGIQ> and <EXPR_LO>

<EXPR_LO>    := | non <EXPR_L>  

<EXPR_L>     := | <EXPR_D>  <=  <EXPR_D>
                | <EXPR_D>  <   <EXPR_D>  
                | <EXPR_D>  =   <EXPR_D>
                | <EXPR_D>  <>  <EXPR_D>
                | <EXPR_D>  >=  <EXPR_D>
                | <EXPR_D>  >   <EXPR_D>

<NOM_IDENT>  := <LETTRE>{<LETTRE OU CHIFFRE OU _ >}  
<PARAM>      := <NOM_IDENT>     
<IDENT_FONC> := <NOM_IDENT>     
<NOM_VAR>    := <NOM_IDENT>     


THE UNARY FONCTIONS  its follow the FORTRAN 77 rules
                     Call of type: abs(x)
     abs    ABSOLUTE VALUE
     sqrt   SQUARE ROOT
     log    NEPERIAN LOGARITHM
     log10  DECIMAL LOGARITHM
     exp    EXPONENT
     asin   ARC SINUS       -pi/2 < =  x < =  pi/2  radians
     acos   ARC COSINUS        0  < =  x < =  pi    radians
     atan   ARC TANGENTE    -pi/2 < =  x < =  pi/2  radians
     sin    SINUS    angle in radians
     cos    COSINUS  angle in radians
     tan    TANGENTE angle in radians
     sinh   HYPERBOLIC SINUS
     cosh   HYPERBOLIC COSINUS
     tanh   HYPERBOLIC TANGENT
     nint   NEAREST INTEGER
                               

THE BINARY FUNCTIONS  its follow the FORTRAN 77 rules
                      Call of type: min(x,y)

     min    MINIMUM of 2 REALS
     max    MAXIMUM of 2 REALS
     mod    mod(i,j)  i modulo j
     isign  isign(x1,x2)= + |x1| if x2 >= 0
                          - |x1| if x2 <  0

     nuobjt nuobjt( 'type_object' , 'nom_object' )
                    'type_object' = | 'point'
                                    | 'ligne'
                                    | 'surface'
                                    | 'volume'
                                    | 'objet'
                                    | 'fonction'
                                    | 'transfo'
            return the number in the directory objet of the object 
                       of name 'nom_object'
                   0 if not recovered

SOME EXAMPLES of LANGAGE LU USING:
==================================
 3 ; 7e5 ;  -(3+4)/7;   { 3 algebraic expressions }

defvar pi,R,circonference;
pi=atan(1) * 4 ; R=1e3 ; circonference= 2 * pi * R ; 
                                      
deffunc g( no , x );
if no=1 then g=no ;
        else g=x ;
endif; 
finfunc; 
g(1,2);              {Calls of the function g}
g(2,3);

deffunc k(n);        { A bad example. Do not use it }
defetiq e1,e2;
aller e2;
e1: k=n*n;
retour;
e2: aller e1;
finfunc;   

DefFunc f(n);        { Example of loop pour }
   defvar i; 
   f=1;
   pour i=1 a n ;
      f=f*i;
   finpour;
EndFunc;
f(5);

deffunc fpur(n);     { franglais }
defvar i,j;
fpur=0;
for i=1 to n;
  for j=1 to 3;
     fpur=fpur+i+j;
  endfor;
finpour;
display fpur;
endfunc;
fpur(2);

DefFunc fa(n);       { Example of while }
   defvar i;
   fa=1; i=0; 
   while i<n ;
      i=i+1 ;
      fa=fa*i ;
   endwhile;
EndFunc; 
fa(5);  

deffunc ftantq(n);   { franglais }
defvar i,j;
ftantq=0;
i=0;
tantque i<n;
   i=i+1;
   j=0;
   while j<=3;
      j=j+1;
      ftantq=ftantq+i+j;
   endwhile;
fintant;
display ftantq;
return;
endfunc;
display ftantq(2);

DefFunc fac(n);      { Example of repeat ... until }
   defvar i;
   fac=1; i=0;
   repeat
      i=i+1; 
      fac=fac*i;
   until i=n;
EndFunc;
fac(5); 
        
deffunc frep(n);     { franglais }
defvar i,j;
frep=0; i=0;
repeat;
  i=i+1; j=0;
  repeter ;
    j=j+1;
    frep=frep+i+j;
  jusque j>4;
until i>=n;
endfunc;
display frep(2);

{Definition of YOUNG module at point x,y,z of this material}
DefFunc young( t, x , y , z , no_type_objet , materiau )
if    materiau=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then young=1e11;
else if    materiau=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
      then young=5e10 ;
      else young=0 ;
      endif;  
endif;
EndFunc; 
young(1,0,0,4,3); 

DefFunc puiss2( n );     { Example of display values }
defvar i;
for i=1 a n;
   display 2**i;
endfor;
EndFunc;
puiss2(16); 
   
deffunc h(n); h=n+n; endfunc; h(5);
{ a function can call an other function }      
deffunc k(n); k=h(h(n)) ; endfunc; k(5);

deffunc maxi(x,y,z);       { Function max with 3 parameters }
  maxi=max(x,max(y,z));
endfunc;

deffunc maxim(x,y,z,t,u);  { Function max with 5 parameters }
  maxim=maxi(x,y,maxi(z,t,u));
endfunc;
maxim(1,2,3,4,5);

deffunc maximum(x,y,z,t,u,v); { Variante with 6 parameters }
  maximum=max(maxi(x,y,maxi(z,t,u)),v);
display maximum;
endfunc;
maximum(1,2,3,6,5,4); 

