=======================================================================  
THE AVAILABLE KEY WORDS AT THIS LEVEL (MENU Debut of the TREE of MENUS)
=======================================================================
 0: EDGE LENGTH by DEFAULT of meshes   
 1: POINTS   define the POINTS of the objects
 2: LINES    define the curves of the objects
 3: SURFACES define the faces of the objects
 4: VOLUMES  materials of the objects
 5: OBJECTS  definition of the objects
 6: MAPPINGS R3-->R3 to use with PLSV
 7: INTERPOLATION choice of Lagrange interpolation degree
                  and definition of NODES of the object mesh

10: DRAWING of PLSVO meshes
May be used at every time.

11: RENAME TAILLE_IDEALE(x,y,z)
Mostly of mesh algorithms use the User's function TAILLE_IDEALE(x,y,z)
which definess the maximum length of finite element edges.
If this function, after to be used, is not adapted for the future
meshes, this function has to be renamed because its presence is sufficient
to be used.

19: min MAX of XYZ of PLSVO or EXTREMAL COORDINATES of PLSVO
To evitate a scaling of drawing after every input, it is advised to
give the minimum and maximum of 3 coordinates of the objects.

20: PRECISION to IDENTIFY POINTS
For every UNION of PLSV, the vertices which belong to 2 PLSV must 
be identified. 2 PRECISIONS have been defined:
- one in the vicinity of the ORIGIN (X Y Z reals lower than EPZERO)
  where an ABSOLUTE TEST is EFFICIENT
- one in the vicinity of any point not closed to ORIGIN
  where a RELATIVE TEST is MORE EFFICIENT
  (one of X Y Z greater than EPZERO)

21: AUTOMATIC UPDATE of the MESHES or NOT
By default, if one of PLSV of the definition of an PLSV is modified,
the mesh is not automatically computed again.
Click on this rectangle to obtain this automatic modification.
Click again on this rectangle to suppress this automatic modification.
ATTENTION: The cost of tests may be important.

39: BACKGROUND COLOR of the WINDOW
To change the color of the Mefisto window

71: TOOLS on TMS
With this option, it is possible to
- DISPLAY a TMS (Tableau Memoire Secondaire = Array on Disk)
- INPUT the values of a TMS
- DISPLAY the VALUE of a TMS variable
- IMPOSE  the VALUE of a TMS variable
- CHANGE  a NAME in a directory

72: TOOLS on FILES of the MS
To add a new file to the MS if it is saturated...

73: TOOLS on I/O units
The option 3 (default value) permits the interaction User-Mefisto

74: DELETE TMS of PLSVO
It is possible to DESTROY a  TMS ou un PLSVO or the function 
TAILLE_IDEALE(x,y,z) ... But no recovering is possible!
Don not use this option.

89: Object from software NEF
Creation for Mefisto of an Object made with the software NEF.
From the input of its NEF name (in upper case) the file NOMOBJECT.XyzNoEF
stored in the project directory is read and the volumes or surfaces, ... 
of this object are created.
Do a Mefisto drawing to see what PLSV compose the object.
The object definition may be modified by the option 5; of this menu.
Do not forget to do the INTERPOLATION 7; to construct the nodes of the mesh

90: File xyznsef of PLSV
Creation of a file xyznsef of tms XYZSOMMET and NSEF of a PLSV 
The values of XYZ of every vertice and the vertex numbers of every FE
are stored in a file xyznsef, readable with a text editor.
This file may be used as interface for other softwares.

91: File xyznpef of an OBJECT
The values of XYZ of every node and the node numbers of every FE
the names of PLSV of vertices, edges, faces and volume of every FE
are stored in a file xyznpef, readable with a text editor.
This file may be used as interface for other softwares.

99: SAVE DATA and QUIT
This option is OBLIGATORY to recover the computed TMS of this
execution during a future execution of MAILLER, THERMICER, ...
ELSE, ALL DATA ARE LOST!...

In this wrong case, see the files FRAPPE.* of the project
which permits to compute again all executions...
But, it is not recommended!...
